The paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for image analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for semi-supervised learning is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the prediction of poverty metrics, which could be considered a form of information retrieval (cs.IR) or geographic information systems (cs.GR).
